#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.164"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.164:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.164:0.2"
msgid "17. Paṭipadāvagga"
msgstr "17. Practice"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: catutthapaṭipadāsuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an4.164:0.3"
msgid "164. Paṭhamakhamasutta"
msgstr "164. Patient (1st)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an4.164:1.1"
msgid "“Catasso imā, bhikkhave, paṭipadā."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are four ways of practice."

msgctxt "an4.164:1.2"
msgid "Katamā catasso?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "an4.164:1.3"
msgid "Akkhamā paṭipadā, khamā paṭipadā, damā paṭipadā, samā paṭipadā."
msgstr ""
"Impatient practice, patient practice, taming practice, and calming practice."

msgctxt "an4.164:1.4"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, akkhamā paṭipadā?"
msgstr "And what’s the impatient practice?"

#. VAR: ekacco → ekacco puggalo (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an4.164:1.5"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco akkosantaṃ paccakkosati, rosantaṃ paṭirosati, "
"bhaṇḍantaṃ paṭibhaṇḍati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when someone abuses, annoys, or argues with you, and you abuse, annoy, "
"or argue right back at them."

msgctxt "an4.164:1.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, akkhamā paṭipadā."
msgstr "This is called the impatient practice."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an4.164:2.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, khamā paṭipadā?"
msgstr "And what’s the patient practice?"

msgctxt "an4.164:2.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco akkosantaṃ na paccakkosati, rosantaṃ na paṭirosati, "
"bhaṇḍantaṃ na paṭibhaṇḍati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when someone abuses, annoys, or argues with you, and you don’t abuse, "
"annoy, or argue back at them."

msgctxt "an4.164:2.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, khamā paṭipadā."
msgstr "This is called the patient practice."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.153"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an4.164:3.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, damā paṭipadā?"
msgstr "And what’s the taming practice?"

msgctxt "an4.164:3.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu cakkhunā rūpaṃ disvā na nimittaggāhī hoti "
"nānubyañjanaggāhī;"
msgstr ""
"When a mendicant sees a sight with their eyes, they don’t get caught up in "
"the features and details."

msgctxt "an4.164:3.3"
msgid ""
"yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ cakkhundriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā "
"pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati; rakkhati "
"cakkhundriyaṃ; cakkhundriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"If the faculty of sight were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of "
"desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they "
"practice restraint, protecting the faculty of sight, and achieving restraint "
"over it."

msgctxt "an4.164:3.4"
msgid "Sotena saddaṃ sutvā … "
msgstr "When they hear a sound with their ears …"

msgctxt "an4.164:3.5"
msgid "ghānena gandhaṃ ghāyitvā … "
msgstr "When they smell an odor with their nose … "

msgctxt "an4.164:3.6"
msgid "jivhāya rasaṃ sāyitvā … "
msgstr "When they taste a flavor with their tongue … "

msgctxt "an4.164:3.7"
msgid "kāyena phoṭṭhabbaṃ phusitvā … "
msgstr "When they feel a touch with their body … "

msgctxt "an4.164:3.8"
msgid "manasā dhammaṃ viññāya na nimittaggāhī hoti nānubyañjanaggāhī;"
msgstr ""
"When they know a thought with their mind, they don’t get caught up in the "
"features and details."

msgctxt "an4.164:3.9"
msgid ""
"yatvādhikaraṇamenaṃ manindriyaṃ asaṃvutaṃ viharantaṃ abhijjhādomanassā "
"pāpakā akusalā dhammā anvāssaveyyuṃ, tassa saṃvarāya paṭipajjati; rakkhati "
"manindriyaṃ; manindriye saṃvaraṃ āpajjati."
msgstr ""
"If the faculty of mind were left unrestrained, bad unskillful qualities of "
"desire and aversion would become overwhelming. For this reason, they "
"practice restraint, protecting the faculty of mind, and achieving restraint "
"over it."

msgctxt "an4.164:3.10"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, damā paṭipadā."
msgstr "This is called the taming practice."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an4.164:4.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, bhikkhave, samā paṭipadā?"
msgstr "And what’s the calming practice?"

msgctxt "an4.164:4.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu uppannaṃ kāmavitakkaṃ nādhivāseti pajahati vinodeti "
"sameti byantīkaroti anabhāvaṃ gameti; uppannaṃ byāpādavitakkaṃ … pe … "
"uppannaṃ vihiṃsāvitakkaṃ … uppannuppanne pāpake akusale dhamme nādhivāseti "
"pajahati vinodeti sameti byantīkaroti anabhāvaṃ gameti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant doesn’t tolerate a sensual, malicious, or cruel "
"thought. They don’t tolerate any bad, unskillful qualities that have arisen, "
"but give them up, get rid of them, calm them, eliminate them, and obliterate "
"them."

msgctxt "an4.164:4.3"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, samā paṭipadā."
msgstr "This is called the calming practice."

msgctxt "an4.164:4.4"
msgid "Imā kho, bhikkhave, catasso paṭipadā”ti."
msgstr "These are the four ways of practice.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.164:4.5"
msgid "Catutthaṃ."
msgstr ""
